    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>You shouldn't have to worry about the stack leaking memory (it is highly uncommon).  The only time you can have the stack get out of control is with infinite (or really deep) recursion.</p>\n\n<p><strong>This is just the heap. Sorry, didn't read your question fully at first.</strong></p>\n\n<p>You need to run the JVM with the following command line argument.</p>\n\n<pre><code>-Xmx&lt;ammount of memory&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>-Xmx1024m\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>That will allow a max of 1GB of memory for the JVM.</p>\n"
  }, {
